column5: Whos been out and what thickness are we talking? Safe for sleds?  Thanks  Heading out Sunday.

I was at simcoe in snake island ice is about 8" in 60ft not sure how much ice in 90ft but I saw a crazy guy driving his car.. his prolly 90ft jigging lol.. I hope he makes it home tonite.. lol It started to snow when i left at 4pm.. 60ft is still perch, caught a herring.. didnt get a white fish..
was out last sat at BP, ice was from 4 to 2.5" saw one sled in 100fow beside me
I was due east of the point yesterday with 6" under me,just watch the cracks....Chuck...
Thanks guys.  Hey Chuck. I,ll be following again sunday.LOL Hope to see ya out there.
